{
  "text": "Bioassay. Lumbar sympathetic or dorsal root ganglia were isolated from embryonic day 9 (E9) chick embryos (Spafas Inc., Roanoke, IL) under sterile conditions in unsupplcmented Ham's F12 medium. After dissection into small pieces (-0.01 mml), explants were transferred to 30 mm polyomithine-coated plastic dishes (2040 explants per dish) containing F12 supplemented with 100 PM putrescinc, 20 nM progesterone, 100 &ml human transfenin, 30 nM selenium, and 2% streptomycin. Dishes were then incubated at 37\u00b0C for 2-3 hr to allow explant attachment, after which known amounts of either rhNGF, rhBDNF, rhNT-3, or human brain extract were added, with or without anti-NGF antibodies. Human brain extract was prepared by homogenizing freshly thawed tissue with an equal volume of Fl2 and centrifuging at 15,000 x g, followed by sterilization of the supematant using a 0.22 pm filter. Extract was added to the dish at 5% of final volume (I .5 ml). Cultures were incubated for an additional 16-18 hr and then fixed and stained with silver nitrate [CITATION_1] .",
  "citation_candidates": [
